  "number": 2074,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2074",
  "title": "Save Search instantsearchjs",
  "body": "I would like to allow users to save their searches.  I have a system in place that parses the URL as an array which allows me to detect what users have been selecting in the facet menu.  I'm using window.location.href.toString() to get the url from the urlsync values.\r\n\r\nSay I have a facet search of cars with BMW and Audi as selectable options.\r\n\r\nif a user visits a page where BMW cars are shown.  If the user then selects Audi, the `window.location.href.toString()` does not update, it still shows BMW.  It's almost as if `window.location.href.toString()` is not being updated although the correct URL is displayed in the address bar.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n{\r\n  url: \"savesearch.php\",\r\n  type: \"POST\",\r\n  data: {\r\n    search_url: window.location.href.toString()\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHas anyone else come across this issue or is there a simpler way to achieve this ?\r\n\r\nMany thanks\r\n\r\nGuy",
